title: Morse's Childhood Love for Gophs is Gone
text:
Morse's Childhood Love for Gophs is Gone 
By Zach Schneider   10:50 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Lakeville, Minn. native Morgan Morse grew up watching the Minnesota women's hockey team, but she says her dream was always to play for its neighbor to the north --- the University of Minnesota Duluth. 
Morse is now a freshman with the Bulldogs, who will be taking on No. 1 Minnesota this weekend, and she's excited for the mini-homecoming. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
"I grew up watching the Gophers and loving the Gophers, but coming here was always my No. 1 choice," she said. "This weekend will be a different perspective having watched them to now being here with our team." 
Both games this weekend will be played at Ridder Arena, with Friday's game set to start at 6:00 p.m. and Saturday's at 4:00 p.m.
